**
** IM7/8552, 134 g/m^2, 59.1% fiber volume fraction, 33% resin content
** Hand layup, autoclave cure at 180 C
** Units: N, mm, s
** Nominal ply thickness: 0.131 mm (actual may be closer to 0.125 mm)
**
** See the file `IM7-8552-C3D.inp` for more details on the material properties
** and references.
**
** Shear nonlinearity coefficients
** Note a: The shear nonlinearity coefficients used here for testing are not
** the values recommended for this material. They are used here for
** testing purposes only. The recommended values for this material are
**
** alpha_PL = 4.06e-9
** n_PL = 5.4
**
** These values are based on fitting the Ramberg-Osgood expression
** to the data reported in:
** C. A. Rose, C. G. Dávila, and F. A. Leone, Analysis methods for progressive
** damage of composite structures, Hampton, VA, NASA/TM–2013-218024, Jul. 2013.
** A. S. Kaddour and M. J. Hinton, Input data for test cases used in
** benchmarking triaxial failure theories of composites, Journal of Composite
** Materials, vol. 46, no. 19–20, Art. no. 19–20, Sep. 2012, doi:
** 10.1177/0021998312449886.
